  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">An integrated Education intervention for Primary and Junior secondary schools in Monguno  Local Government Area of Borno state</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This integrated project plans to as its main objective to improve access to quality education to conflict affected boys and girls in four (4) selected school in Monguno LGA of Borno state.
The boys and girls aged between (3-17) who from the assessment conducted at Monguno where discovered to lack access to safe and protective learning environment, Kabhuda intends to provide access to this children through the following strategies.  

1. Provision of temporary classrooms at 4 schools in Monguno LGA and the New (28 TLS amp 14 Latrines)
2. Provision of latrines and hand washing kits in 4 selected schools of Monguno. 
3. Provision of teaching and learning supplies to 1007 children in Monguno. 
4. Hygiene dignity kits for 500 Adolescent girls in Monguno. 
5. Training of teachers on psycho social support services and pedagogy. 
6. Training and support for SBMC. 
The goal of this integrated project is to provide a comprehensive intervention in partnership with government and relative stakeholder to  addresses school structure gaps, WASH gaps, gaps on teaching and learning supplies, hygiene gaps on adolescent girls and lack of teacher capacity.</narrative>
  </description>
